criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Malignant tumor patients with clear pathological diagnosis;

               -  Those who have no serious primary diseases of the cardiovascular,
                  cerebrovascular, respiratory, endocrine, urinary, blood and other systems;

                    -  The main organs (hematopoiesis, heart, lung, liver, and kidney) have no
                       obvious abnormal function; ④Age ≥18 years old, ≤75 years old; ⑤ No serious
                       eye disease;

                         -  The patient volunteered to participate in this study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with severe blood loss (because when the bleeding exceeds 300ml, the white
             eye color of the patient is often pale white);

               -  Poor patient compliance; ③ pregnant and lactating women;

                    -  Can't cooperate with inspection properly; ⑤ Cannot read or understand the
                       scale.
